pull.title: qt, refactor: Use proper classes for Ui::*
pull.body:
Use proper classes for:
- `Ui::ModalOverlay` to remove `<customwidget>` entry
- `Ui::ReceiveCoinsDialog` to be consistent with the code base

This PR does not change behavior.

comments.diff_hunk:
@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@
 <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
 <ui version="4.0">
  <class>ModalOverlay</class>
- <widget class="ModalOverlay" name="ModalOverlay">
+ <widget class="QWidget" name="ModalOverlay">
comments.body: Right, a customwidget entry for the top-level widget is always unnecessary, as it's not instantiated by the generated code.
